We are excited to announce that DESE recently released information regarding the extension of the Summer Food Service Program (SFSP).
Beginning Tuesday, September 8th, Risco RII School District will be offering breakfast and lunch to anyone under the age of 18, FREE OF CHARGE. This program will extend through December or until funds are no longer available. If you are not a student and would like to participate, please contact the high school office for details.

post_text:
Tomorrow is our first day back to school. We can't wait to see our students!
Below are a few reminders:
-Please keep your child home if they are feeling ill.
-Temperatures will be checked at the door.
-Students will not be allowed to enter the building until 7:30 a.m..
-Please have your child bring a water bottle for our refillable water stations.
-Pre-K and Kindergarten parents will be allowed to walk their child into the Cafeteria on the 1st day of school. A temperature check and mask will be required.
- Grades 3rd -12th will report to their 1st hour class for breakfast in the classroom.

post_text:
Just a reminder to parents that if your child is entering K, 8th or 12th grade, Missouri law requires the following vaccinations.

K- MMR and Varicella 2nd dose
8th- TDAP and Meningococcal
12th- Meningococcal

These must be done prior to August 24th, the first day of school. Please verify that your child's immunizations are up to date.

If needing immunizations, your local health department can help. Our local New Madrid office can be reached at 573-748-5541.

Thank you!

post_text:
I wanted to take this opportunity to make you all aware of the personnel and procedural changes we are making in the elementary this year.

Ms. Jessie King will now be teaching Kindergarten for us this year.

Also beginning this year instead of being departmentalized 4th - 6th grade we will now be departmentalized for 3rd/4th and then 5th/6th.

Ms. Missy Bedwell will now be our 3rd Grade home room teacher and will be teaching English Language Arts & Social Studies for 3rd & 4th grades.

Ms. Kimberly Jones will be our 4th grade home room teacher and will be teaching Math & Science for 3rd & 4th grades.

Ms. Samantha Craft will be our 5th grade home room teacher and will be teaching Math & Science for 5th & 6th grades.

Ms. Rebecca Pilsing will be our 6th grade home room teacher and will be teaching English Language Arts & Social Studies for 5th & 6th grade.

post_text:
Risco School Community,

Due to the most recent announcement from the Governor to close the remainder of the school year, our online learning will continue until May 7th. Our breakfast/lunch program will also continue until May 7th.

I know everyone has questions about graduation, prom, and important end of the year events. We are gathering information and still in discussion at this time. We will let you know as soon as we have answers.

I know this year did not end how anyone expected. I also know that our students missed out on celebrating many of their important milestones. But, I also know that we are a strong, supportive and caring school family who will get through this. I am so proud of how our students, parents and staff came together during this challenging time. You all stepped out of your comfort zone and made things happen with a very short notice! I am super proud to be your leader, but even more proud to be a Risco Tiger! Stay safe and healthy everyone!

Sincerely,

Dr. Baker

post_text:
Dear School Community,

The superintendents of all New Madrid County Schools: Risco, Gideon, Portageville and New Madrid County R-1 have collaborated and decided to follow the federal guidelines and extend our closure through April 30, 2020, with the current plan to return Friday, May 1 if possible.

We will continue feeding students with a Monday and Wednesday pick up time (between 11:00-12:00), resuming April 6th. We will also be providing a variety of educational opportunities for students during this time. You will recieve more information towards the end of the week about our online learning platform.

Again, there is no higher priority than the safety of our students and community. Although there are no reported cases in our county, the rising number of cases surrounding us is concerning. We will continually update you with the most recent information and changes.

Sincerely,
Dr. Amy Baker

Just wanted to say Congrats to these 3 guys for earning Tri-County All Conference honors! After graduating 6 seniors last year who combined for 67ppg (including the all-time leading scorer in school history), most people thought we would be below .500 and one of the bottom teams in our area. These young men led our team to our 5th straight Conference championship game appearance and a second place finish in the regular season conference standings (2 points away from a repeat as regular season conference champions). These guys battled and improved as a team and as individuals! I appreciate all the hard work they put in this year!
Andrew Rodgers - 1st Team All Conference
Kamron Meese - 1st Team All Conference
Evan Pipkin - Honorable Mention All-Conference

Please be sure to bring: Birth certificate, current immunization record, social security number and proof of residency. Priority for PreK enrollment is given to in-district 4 year olds. Kg.must be 5 before August 1, 2020.

The New Madrid County WIC office will be here from 8:30-2:30 to see if anyone would be interested in WIC.

Aneliese Cox Kennedy
February 5 at 7:52 PM ·

Risco FBLA made me one proud adviser today! They came dressed for success with a world of opportunity in reach! The group set up for the awards ceremony, made trips loading and unloading, Mackenzie ran the registration table all day, and then the entire group picked up trash that was left behind in Academic. They were true business leaders and it didn't stop with just service!

We have two district officers for next year and won eleven medals.

Emma Hicks - District President (for the second year), 1st Future Business Leader, 1st Personal Finance, 3rd Accounting; Ashlynn Presley- Vice President of FBLA-PBL Relations, 4th Intro to Financial Math, 4th Intro to FBLA; Cesar Marquez - 1st Economics; Dalton Hayes - 1st Accounting; Molly Fortner - 2nd Intro to Financial Math; 4th Intro to Business Communication; Carlye Shultz - 2nd Intro to Business Communication; Jocelyn Calvert & Abbi Garris - 5th Emerging Business Issues

post_text:
The Risco Jr high and High school softball teams are selling X-Grain sportswear merchandise to help raise money for the softball teams. While there is no quota for us to sell, $5 of each item sold will be given back to the teams and used for equipment. Thanks in advance to everyone who orders! Attached is the link to purchase any of the items you may want.

Note: when purchasing be sure you are selecting the item you desire. Some items are duplicates with the word “softball” under the logo. Please check sizing charts prior to purchasing. You will deal directly with the company and they do not accept returns as each item is customized. All orders will be shipped to the school, a pick up date will be announced once we get the items in.

https://stores.inksoft.com/WS32288
